Configure alternating pages during pagination of a clintable

Source: R/pagination.R
clin_alt_pages.Rd

This function configures alternating pages on a clintable object.

Usage

clin_alt_pages(x, key_cols, col_groups)

Arguments

x

A clintable object

key_cols

A character vector of variable names

col_groups

A list of character vectors of variable names

byvar

A variable in the input dataset to use for pagination settings

max_rows

The maximum number of rows to include on a page

Value

A clintable object

Examples

ct <- clintable(mtcars)

clin_alt_pages(
  ct,
  key_cols = c('mpg', 'cyl', 'hp'),
  col_groups = list(
    c('disp', 'drat', 'wt'),
    c('qsec', 'vs', 'am'),
    c('gear', 'carb')
  )
)
#> NOTE: Alternating pages were set, but no selection for row wise pagination was configured Defaulting to 20 rows per page.
